      "content": "but \"without the finality\" is the problem. that's just more fighting. more doctors, more pills that don't work, more years of this... it's not relief, it's just delaying the inevitable. if the only way to actually stop the noise is to make it permanent, isn't that just being realistic? isn't there some kind of mercy in just being allowed to stop?",
